All Implemented Interfaces:
DomainRenderer, ComponentRenderer<Field>, DomainPlugIn, PlugIn
public abstract class AbstractSelectRenderer
extends AbstractDomainRenderer

An abstract base class for all renderers that are used to render form controls for the selection of data. Concrete subclasses of this class can be configured as "select-renderer" plug-ins in the domain configuration. A select renderer is used when a field has a target path and an options path.

Custom select renderers should extend either this class or another renderer implementation that extends this class. Do not extend the AbstractDomainRenderer class or the attempt to implement directly the DomainRenderer interface.

Method Detail

getName

public java.lang.String getName()
Gets the name of the plug-in. This is usually the simple name used to identify the plug-in when loaded. Many different plug-in classes may share the same name if they implement the same type of behavior. For example, "converter" may be used as the name of a plug-in that performs data conversion operations, but there may be different "converter" classes implementing these operations.

Returns:
The plug-in name "select-renderer".
